# cppcheck suppressions for the `make cppcheck` hard gate (scans all headers).
# Each entry is a deliberate, justified design pattern -- not a defect. Revisit
# if the design changes. Format: <id>[:<file-glob>[:<line>]].

# Policy-based design (Modern C++ Design style): trainable / quantized layer and
# connection variants intentionally re-declare same-named compile-time members
# and methods from their base policy -- e.g. IsTrainable=true overriding the
# base IsTrainable=false. The shadowing is the mechanism, not a mistake.
duplInheritedMember

# Byte-pool storage members are raw unsigned-char buffers populated by
# placement-new, and the layer pointers into them are assigned in the
# constructor body; none are read before being set. cppcheck's
# member-initializer-list check cannot see the body initialization. Scoped to
# the two files that use the byte-pool pattern so genuine uninitialized members
# elsewhere still fail the gate.
uninitMemberVar:*/kan.hpp
uninitMemberVar:*/qlearn.hpp
